Dear DDJ Reader,

D-Flat and D-Flat++ are the popular DOS text-mode CUA/SAA- 
compliant C/C++ windowing libraries Al Stevens has developed over 
the past couple of years in his "C Programming" column. This disk 
contains full source code of the most recent versions of both 
libraries. D-Flat/D-Flat++, which deliver the CUA interface in an 
event-driven architecture, supports applications windows, child 
development windows, menu bars, pop down menus, dialog boxes, 
buttons, and more. 
      You can compile D-Flat with the Watcom, Microsoft, and 
Borland C compilers. This version of D-Flat++ compiles only 
Borland C++, however.
       For details on the libraries themselves, see the
README.DOC files in the appropriate subdirectories. Note that
detailed programmer's notes for D-Flat are provided in the
file DFLAT.DOC.
       We'd love to hear how you are using D-Flat, D-Flat++,
and other programs presented in Dr. Dobb's Journal. (Maybe
you could even write an article about your projects.) Give us a 
call, write a letter, or send us some E-mail (CompuServe 
76704,50).
               
Jonathan Erickson
editor-in-chief

     

